## Recommended Progression Path

If you are working through these extensions as a learning journey, this order makes the most sense:

```
Current state (0D on-design)
        │
        ▼
Extension 2 — Emissions             (~20 lines, data already in Cantera — do this first)
        │
        ▼
Extension 3 — Turbofan cycle        (build intuition for the CF34 deck; use it as validation)
        │
        ▼
Extension 1 — Off-design maps       (component matching — core turbomachinery concept)
        │
        ▼
Extension 6 — Mean-line design      (bridges cycle → blade geometry)
        │
        ▼
Extension 4 — Turboprop/Turboshaft  (small incremental step, opens up helicopter/UAV domain)
        │
        ▼
Extension 8 — Mission analysis      (connects engine performance to aircraft-level metrics)
        │
        ▼
Extension 7 — Surrogate / ML        (accelerates design space exploration across all above)
        │
        ▼
Extension 5 — Hybrid electric       (system-level integration, brings everything together)
        │
        ▼
Extension 9 — Noise                 (add-on at any stage once nozzle data is available)
```

Each step uses the previous one as its foundation. The progression moves from thermodynamics → turbomachinery → aircraft systems → advanced propulsion — which mirrors the natural curriculum of an aerospace propulsion programme.

